    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Italian wood benches with a chest under the seat, in the form of a large cassone with back and arms added to form a settee or sofa with storage below. Loose cushions were used for comfort. The form was popular in Florence. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
